---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About — hookbook.dev">
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 prose">
    <h1>About hookbook.dev</h1>

    <p>hookbook.dev is a curated, honestly-labeled cookbook for <a href="https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/claude-code/hooks">Claude Code hooks</a>. Built by <a href="https://github.com/Rogue899">Tarek Roukoz</a> as a community contribution and ongoing operator's journal.</p>

    <h2>Why this exists</h2>
    <p>Anthropic documents 29 hook events. Community tutorials cover 6 to 8. The other ~21 are nearly invisible in public content. This site closes that gap with curated recipes, trust labels, and pitfall explainers.</p>

    <h2>What it isn't</h2>
    <p>An exhaustive awesome-list — those exist already and we link to them. A reference replacement for the official Anthropic docs — those are authoritative and we link to them. A subscription product — MIT licensed, no monetization, no Pro tier.</p>

    <h2>How to contribute</h2>
    <p>Open a PR with your recipe. The trust label will be downgraded to <em>experimental</em> on merge. See <a href="https://github.com/Rogue899/hookbook/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md">CONTRIBUTING.md</a>.</p>

    <h2>Who built this</h2>
    <p>hookbook.dev is built and maintained by <a href="https://github.com/Rogue899">Tarek Roukoz</a>, a senior software engineer focused on AI systems and multi-agent orchestration. The cookbook started as personal infrastructure for his own Claude Code workflow and grew into a community contribution.</p>
    <p>If you're hiring AI engineers or want to collaborate on agentic infrastructure, reach out via <a href="https://github.com/Rogue899">GitHub</a>.</p>

    <h2>Companion projects</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/Rogue899/hookbook">GitHub repo</a> — source + recipes</li>
    </ul>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
